data.meta_description: 1,031 likes, 47 comments - forgottenseasonsnba on July 19, 2020: "Peak Andrew Bynum was one of the biggest forces in the league. At just 24 years old, he was one of 3 players in 2011/12 to average at least 18ppg and 11rpg (Love, Howard). Bynum was also named an All-Star starter in his lone ASG appearance. This season was pretty much the last we saw of him. Bynum missed the entire next season with knee problems, and played just 26 games for the rest of his career. He was such a tantalizing talent; a giant athletic big man with a feathery soft touch. It’s a shame he couldn’t stay healthy. He would have been one of the best bigs in the league for a long time. SWIPE ➡️ for highlights and images.".
